Paging all web3 wizards here! @chromalita @richerd @dotta @m3mnoch @stevefink

... Then consensus was reached on the second evaluation and this was written into the blockchain, but somehow OS, our frontend and the bot picked up the events, broadcasted by the first node as well.

No idea if that works but would love feedback on that guess, to keep learning.

My guess: Maybe some node evaluated the contract, came to a conclusion and broadcasted a mint transaction which included zID. Another node did the same thing, but coming to a different conclusion of which tokens were minted (we're using pseudo-randomness to mint randomly)...
The big mysterious thing here is: Where did the three events, that triggered the tools above to shout out the zombie mint, come from and where did they go to? https://t.co/REFryNco4y

But looking at the contract events shows (as to be expected) three events tied to the mint transaction. Crosschecking the minted token ids (third line) matches them to the one we saw in the mint transaction... https://t.co/uLZRhCcEn5

So why did OpenSea emit the token in their frontend, our webpage show the token in reveal and our minting bot post about it in #minting-and-trading? 
My first guess: All those tools listen to contract events to do their thing so maybe we had a fuckup there...

OpenSea is still showing token zID as unrevealed, which is weird on its own, as all xPunks are revealed pre mint and the metadata stored on IPFS. Querying the contract directly shows why that is: The token does not exist yet... https://t.co/yzZGnFTiTC

Digging further in. First let‚Äôs have a look at the actual transaction https://t.co/wlIFYDJmC4 ... Etherscan is pretty adamant: token zID was not minted here). Checking the owner wallet confirms that: It matches 4 tokens bought before and the three minted in tx above... https://t.co/WkHODIOHku

A quick check on OpenSea revealed on their platform they received 5! ExpansionPunks: The three currently shown on https://t.co/CXh4uaMZ1L and two unrevealed, where the tokenIds match the zombie tokenId (#17459, let‚Äôs call it zID)... https://t.co/d44chvAR1m

What happened: Someone minted 3 ExpansionPunks and when revealing was shown a really cool zombie (among the other two). When heading to their account page on our site, suddenly, lo and behold, there were three different xPunks ... https://t.co/jYuyTv8lSS
So we had something *interesting* happen today, when one community member minted 3 @ExpansionPunks . If you are experiences with #web3 & #evm would love some insight if my theory is correct üßµ
